- Mon 25 Nov 2019. CMRE (Comite Multisectoriel de la Riposte a la maladie a virus Ebola)
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://mailchi.mp/efbbc78e9cfd/situation-pidmiologique-du-16-novembre-3759593?e=37a53d5a9e

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 24 Nov 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 3303, of which 3185 are confirmed and 118 are probable. In total, there have been 2199 deaths (2081 in confirmed and 118 in probable cases) and 1077 people have recovered.
- 314 suspected cases under investigation;
- 2 new confirmed cases in North Kivu, including 1 in Beni and 1 in Oicha;
- 1 new death of a confirmed case, in Oicha, North Kivu; no community deaths reported among confirmed cases;
- no recovered patients have been released from ETCs;
- no health worker is among the new confirmed cases. The cumulative number of confirmed/probable cases among health workers is 163 (5% of all confirmed/probable cases), including 41 deaths.

Vaccination
-----------
- 597 people were vaccinated, until Fri 22 Nov 2019, with the 2nd Ad26.ZEBOV/MVA-BN-Filo vaccine (Johnson & Johnson) in the 2 health zones of Karisimbi in Goma;
- since vaccination began on 8 Aug 2018 with the rVSV-ZEBOV vaccine, until Sun 24 Nov 2019, 255 136 people have been vaccinated;
- approved on 22 Oct 2019 by the Ethics Committee of the School of Public Health of the University of Kinshasa and 23 Oct 2019 by the National Ethics Committee, the 2nd vaccine, called Ad26.ZEBOV/MVA-BN -Filo, is produced by Janssen Pharmaceuticals for Johnson & Johnson;
- this new vaccine is in addition to the 1st, the rVSV-ZEBOV, vaccine used until then (since 8 Aug 2018) in this epidemic manufactured by the pharmaceutical group Merck, after approval of the Ethics Committee on 20 May 2018. It has recently been pre-qualified for registration.

Monitoring at entry points
--------------------------
- since the beginning of the epidemic, the total number of travelers checked (temperature measurement) at the sanitary control points is 120 481 150;

